  <scopecontent id="aspace_8bbb906e5f827689abc9820b4e65f8da">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Printing equipment and supplies, including 18th century pattern, French style, type mould, 18 point body; ladle; slotted screwdriver; punch, letter P; strike, from P punch; fitted matrix, from P punch; cast sorts, using new mould. Also, matrices for upper- and lower-case letters, a carved wood block, copper plates for engravings, a composer's stick, galley, chase, type cases, a passage of text set up in type, screens for use in hand paper making, and a book binding loom. Also, two metal sheets used in offset printing for the August 16, 1968 issue of a newspaper, the Ithaca Journal.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_d0cc106ecf03e8b08e229c3cdda7a9a0">
    <head>RELATED MATERIALS</head>
<p>For samples of paper, parchment, and printed materials, see <title>Collection of teaching materials for book history</title>, Z240 .C69</p>  </relatedmaterial>
